bio: When I first decided architecture was the career path I was going to strive for, my reasons were much different than they are now. I longed for the ability to leave something on the earth that would still be here one hundred years from now, convinced if my buildings stood the test of time my architecture would be the best. After I finished school my views changed drastically. Since I was younger I had continuously reassured myself of my subliminal passion for designing and building. My favorite toys consisted of Lincoln Logs and Legos when I was very young, up to erector sets and much more complex toys when I grew older. During my adolescent years I began spending hours on the computer with different design programs like The Sims and the infamously terrible Home Designer 6.0. Then I discovered the real world of 3D modeling, AutoCAD and Rhinoceros 3D NURBS modeling. Those around me became uninterested with these programs after short period of time, but I carried on, obsessed with the ability to create space at my fingertips. We are in a progressive era now, and everything is done on or by computers. Luckily for the architectural horizon my passions and disciplines involve using computers heavily. With a reclaimed plastic Olfa knife in hand and paper recycling bin nestled under my desk, I will move forward into this new age of architectural design and find my place among my colleagues in this sustainable revolution, or should I say, evolution.

bio:
Designer, Maker, Builder, Hacker and Programmer for anything from simple circuit builds to working with high-end commercial systems and specialist networking and server gear and everything in between.

Owner of heavily customized & upgraded RepRapPro Tri-Colour Mendel (Prusa-Mendel) which gives me 3 extruders and hot ends side by side to print in 3 glorious colours or/and materials in a single print job non stop on a 225x225mm print bed.
Also own a FlashForge Finder which is an incredibly accurate machine that puts down obscenely detailed and intricate prints that most $1500+ machines don't print as well. It may be a low cost machine, but it doesn't act like one. It is fast becoming my goto printer for any jobs up to 150mm cubed.

Also own a few self builds and modified machines that have been tinkered with over the years that mostly get used for basic parts and fittings.

I own 2 HPC/LaserScript 3020 water cooled Co2 Laser cutters/engravers. One is the older model and the other is the current revision. Both are great machines and serious work horses!

Worked almost exclusively in Signals, Engineering, Telecommunications and Communications from age 17 to now in my late 30's being one of the lead engineers and goto troubleshooters on the ground overseeing the LTE and other new gen mobile data services roll out across the South of the UK..

Am very much into Engineering and Electronics, Programming and IT at home as well as work, I enjoy working with both State of the Art new tech and Retro electronics and IT from the 70's and 80's, I am especially happy when I can combine the two and use old school parts for modern uses and vice versa.
Love photography, again both modern digital and classic 60's to late 70's & some early 80's 35mm film. Owner of a nice collection of Minolta 35mm Cameras fixed lens and SLR (including some super rare cameras and lenses and use all of them often alongside my Lumix Digital setup.
Big supporter of Open Source Hardware and Software as well as supporting Internet Privacy and paid up member of EFF helping keep our Internet open and uncensored!

Till recently was an avid PC gamer, I still play FPS and RTS games from time to time but gave up alot after I realized the amount of time a month I was dedicating to Gaming instead of doing productive activities.
I bought myself an XBox One for my birthday last year and throw that on for a few hours a couple of times a week to play Battlefield, Titanfall 2, Gears and Halo, to name a few...

Enjoy most designing and building Electronic projects from LED coloured lighting displays to high spec robotics.

Am a Big time user of the Arduino family and also of the Raspberry Pi and Beaglebone platforms. I own far too many dev boards and similar. Including a whole stack of RasPi running 24/7 all running needed programs and services.
I also own boards by Udoo, Onion, Espruino, WiPy and Particle.

I like to work in the grey areas between my day job and my hobbies and to do so I do a little PenTesting and System Auditing privately under my own small design, prototyping and IT company '@t #ashtag' (At Hashtag or @#). I love finding holes in systems and figuring out ways to patch and prevent them. Supporter of HAK5 and their products as well as many other professional and legal Black Hat companies and groups working to expose holes in systems and provide solutions to fix them.
Under the same banner I also take on sub contracting jobs to bring other peoples ideas to life through design and prototyping as well as small batch production.

Full supporter of all things relating to the Internet of Things

Proud owner of 2 self built RoboBrrds and a small battalion of other self built robots in many forms that often evolve when new hardware becomes available.

Big supporter of Linux as a primary OS and related opensource projects.

I love GOOD TV and Film and am a big fan of Bad Robot Productions TV Series inc Fringe, Lost, Colony, etc... I also love good British Drama like Line of Duty, Broadchurch, Sherlock, Night Manager and so on.

I enjoy reading and am a MASSIVE Discworld fan. I own every book from Terry Pratchett's series and most of the other related media including a big collection of Clarecraft, Paul Kidby, Peter Denis, Bernard Pearson & Josh Kirby (and various other artists) DW Art & design. Discworld is probably the biggest influence on my life and has been the only constant throughout my Adult life since I picked up Colour of Magic in around 1993/4.

I have a full Firearms certificate and love shooting, beit Target or Hunting with Air Rifles at 50-60 yards to shooting .17HMR and .22 Rimfire targets at 100+ meters as well as Clay Pigeon and Hunting with Shotguns (I have a love of small bore shotguns in 20 gauge and 410 as it makes things a little more interesting)...
Dog lover and have a Jack Russell terrier named Harkness after 'Cpt Jack Harkness' from Torchwood and Dr Who (2 of my favorite shows ever) who I enjoy taking out in the woods for a lark around! He is also a fully trained gun dog and retriever (even though that does not always mean he hands over what he retrieves...) He is a great and loyal dog and companion.

Why SHdesign?
SHdesign originated in 2012 from a need to be able to share designs and projects with everyone who is interested in this.

From my own hobbies and interests for new techniques I started to combine these with each other. Because of this I started to make practical designs to support the model flying hobby.
There was a lot of interest in the designs at the various events and soon a demand arose to start producing them.
Producing my designs is a step too far for me. That is why I opted for the "Share, Use & Remix" concept.

All designs are published on this website and may be used freely by anyone under the Creative Commons CC - BY - NC conditions.

Make it yourself!
The designs I made / modified can be made at most FabLabs. If you do not have a 3D printer or laser cutter yourself, the FabLab machines can be used for a small fee.

All affiliated FabLabs can be found on the website of the umbrella FabLab Benelux organization. There is probably also one in your area.

Waarom SHdesign ?
SHdesign is in 2012 ontstaan uit een behoefte om ontwerpen en projecten te kunnen delen met iedereen die hierin geïnteresseerd is.

Vanuit mijn eigen hobby’s en interesses voor nieuwe technieken ben ik deze met elkaar gaan combineren. Hierdoor ben ik begonnen om praktische ontwerpen te maken voor de ondersteuning van de modelvlieghobby.
Op de verschillende evenementen was er veel interesse voor de ontwerpen en ontstond al snel een vraag om deze te gaan produceren.
Het produceren van mijn ontwerpen is voor mij een stap te ver. Vandaar dat ik voor het “Share, Use & Remix” concept gekozen heb.

Op deze website worden alle ontwerpen gepubliceerd en mogen onder de Creative Commons voorwaarde CC – BY – NC door iedereen vrij gebruikt worden.

Zelf maken !
De door mij gemaakte / aangepaste ontwerpen kunnen bij de meeste FabLab’s gemaakt worden. Als je zelf niet de beschikt over een 3D printer of lasersnijder, kunnen de machines van het FabLab tegen een kleine vergoeding gebruikt worden.

Op de website van de overkoepelende FabLab Benelux organisatie zijn alle aangesloten FabLab’s te vinden. Waarschijnlijk is er ook één bij u in de buurt.

Most of the time I live in the real world but sometimes I get to go to the 3D Printing World where conventional rules don’t apply, your thoughts can become a reality and you can make some really stupid pointless crap. Actually it's not pointless or stupid as it's a lot of fun and you will learn along the way.

I always hear people say "making functional things are their favorite" but I get to that all day at work. When I go to the 3D Printing World I want to spend my time making things I think are fun, interesting, and had just previously been a figment of my ridiculous imagination.

When I’m in the real world I’m a Design Engineer at Projects Designed and Built Inc. We design and build custom machines and automation for many different industries for any application. We are located in Toledo, OH but we have machinery located all over the world. PD&B is a great place to work and being a custom machine designer for a small business is really the ideal job for a Maker. Sometimes I just can’t believe I’m being paid to do something that is so fun that I would do for free.

  3D PRINTING SERVICE:

  VINYL & STICKER SERVICE:

I've been an artist in some form for most of my life. 3D modeling is my latest outlet for that...

I currently run 4 printers at home:

  • Formlabs Form 2
  • FolgerTech FT-5
  • STG-1, my own custom 12" x 12" x 16" printer.
  • STG-2, a speed-optimized 12" x 8" x 16" printer (Volcano hot end with a 1mm nozzle, printing 0.8mm layers)

My prints are almost always heavily post-processed: sanding, filler, painting, electronics, etc... you will VERY rarely see anything intended to be used raw. As such I print in a pretty small range of colors: clear, black, white and silver are about it.
